 the\nlow--mass end, where quenching might be driven by causes external to the\ngalaxies; the other, at the high--mass end, where quenching is driven by\ninternal causes, very likely the mass given the low scatter of $\\Sigma_1$ (mass\nquenching). We suggest that the monotonic increase of central density as\ngalaxies grow is one manifestation of a more general phenomenon of structural\ntransformation that galaxies undergo as they evolve.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Jun 2017 18:00:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 28 Dec 2017 07:30:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-14"}
