{"id":"1706.02486","submitter":"Emil Vosmar Denning","authors":"Emil V. Denning, Jake Iles-Smith, Dara P. S. McCutcheon, Jesper Mork","title":"Protocol for generating multi-photon entangled states from quantum dots\n  in the presence of nuclear spin fluctuations","comments":null,"journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. A 96, 062329 (2017)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.96.062329","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Multi-photon entangled states are a crucial resource for many applications in\nquantum information science. Semiconductor quantum dots offer a promising route\nto generate such states by mediating photon-photon correlations via a confined\nelectron spin, but dephasing caused by the host nuclear spin environment\ntypically limits coherence (and hence entanglement) between photons to the spin\n$T_2^*$ time of a few nanoseconds. We propose a protocol for the deterministic\ngeneration of multi-photon entangled states that is inherently robust against\nthe dominating slow nuclear spin environment fluctuations, meaning that\ncoherence and entanglement is instead limited only by the much longer spin\n$T_2$ time of microseconds. Unlike previous protocols, the present scheme\nallows for the generation of very low error probability polarisation encoded\nthree-photon GHZ states and larger entangled states, without the need for spin\necho or nuclear spin calming techniques.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Jun 2017 09:20:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 27 Oct 2017 09:22:23 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 30 Oct 2017 06:51:23 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 3 Jan 2018 13:37:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-01-10"}
